{"pageProps":{"tutorial":{"title":"CSS Margins","slug":"css-margins","subject":"CSS","category":"Web Development","level":"Beginner","estimated_read_time":"10 mins","prerequisites":["CSS Borders"],"learning_objectives":["Understand what margins are","Control space outside elements","Use individual side properties","Use the margin shorthand property","Understand margin collapse"],"theory":"The CSS `margin` properties are used to create space around elements, **outside** of any defined borders.\n\nMargins are transparent (they have no background color).\n\nYou can specify margins for each side: `margin-top`, `margin-right`, `margin-bottom`, `margin-left`.","syntax":"/* Shorthand: top right bottom left */\nmargin: 25px 50px 75px 100px;\n\n/* Shorthand: vertical horizontal */\nmargin: 25px 50px;\n\n/* Center an element */\nmargin: auto;","examples":[{"code":"div {\n  width: 300px;\n  margin: auto;\n  border: 1px solid red;\n}","output":"A 300px wide red box horizontally centered in its container.","explanation":"`margin: auto` calculates equal left and right margins to center block elements."}],"common_mistakes":[{"mistake":"Confusing margin and padding","correction":"Margin is OUTSIDE the border. Padding is INSIDE the border.","example":"See Box Model for details."}],"interview_questions":[{"question":"What is margin collapse?","answer":"When two vertical margins meet, they collapse into a single margin equal to the largest of the two, rather than adding up.","difficulty":"Hard"}],"practice_problems":[{"problem":"Give a div 20px margin on top and bottom, and 10px on left and right using shorthand.","hint":"Two value syntax.","solution":"margin: 20px 10px;","difficulty":"Easy"}],"real_world_use_cases":[{"scenario":"Spacing Components","description":"Margins are the primary way to create whitespace between article paragraphs, buttons, and sections.","code":".btn + .btn { margin-left: 10px; }"}],"exam_notes":["Margins can have negative values (used for overlapping).","Sho